@comment ===============================================================
@node Init File, Multilingual Char, Options, Invocation
@section .emacs ’¤Î’¥µ’¥ó’¥×’¥ë
@cindex .emacs
@cindex ’¥«’¥¹’¥¿’¥Þ’¥¤’¥º[’¤«’¤¹’¤¿’¤Þ’¤¤’¤º]
@cindex init file

Mule ’¤Ï’µ¯’Æ°’»þ’¤Ë’³Æ’¼«’¤Î’¥Û’¡¼’¥à’¥Ç’¥£’¥ì’¥¯’¥È’¥ê’¤Ë’¤¢’¤ë @file{.emacs} ’¤È’¤¤’¤¦
’½é’´ü’²½’¥Õ’¥¡’¥¤’¥ë(Init file)’¤ò’»²’¾È’¤·’¤Þ’¤¹’¡£’¤³’¤Î’¥Õ’¥¡’¥¤’¥ë’¤Ë Lisp ’¥×’¥í’¥°’¥é’¥à
’¤ò’µ­’½Ò’¤·’¤Æ’¤ª’¤¯’¤³’¤È’¤Ë’¤è’¤ê’¡¢Mule ’¤ò’ÆÈ’¼«’¤Ë’¥«’¥¹’¥¿’¥Þ’¥¤’¥º’¤¬’¤Ç’¤­’¤ë’¤è’¤¦’¤Ë’¤Ê’¤ê’¤Þ
’¤¹’¡£@refill

Mule ’¤Ï Nemacs ’¤È’¤Ï’¸ß’´¹’À­’¤¬’¤Ê’¤¤’¤¿’¤á’¡¢Nemacs ’ÍÑ’¤Î @file{.emacs} ’¤Ï’¤½’¤Î’¤Þ
’¤Þ’¤Ç’¤Ï’¥¨’¥é’¡¼’¤ò’µ¯’¤³’¤¹’²Ä’Ç½’À­’¤¬’¤¢’¤ê’¤Þ’¤¹’¡£’°Ê’²¼’¤Ë’¡¢Mule ’¤È Nemacs(’¤½’¤·’¤Æ GNU
Emacs ’¤â)’¤Ç’¶¦’ÄÌ’¤·’¤Æ’»È’ÍÑ’¤Ç’¤­’¤ë @file{.emacs} ’¤Î’´Ê’Ã±’¤Ê’Îã’¤ò’¼¨’¤·’¤Þ’¤¹’¡£@refill

’¤¿’¤À’¤·’¡¢byte-compile ’¤¹’¤ë’¾ì’¹ç’¤Ï’Ãí’°Õ’¤·’¤Ê’¤±’¤ì’¤Ð’¤Ê’¤ê’¤Þ’¤»’¤ó’¡£Mule ’¤È Nemacs 
’¤Ç’¤Ï’´Á’»ú’¤Î’Æâ’Éô’É½’¸½’¤¬’°ã’¤¤’¤Þ’¤¹’¤Î’¤Ç’¡¢’¥³’¥á’¥ó’¥È’°Ê’³°’¤Ë’´Á’»ú’Ê¸’»ú’Îó’¤ò’´Þ’¤à emacs
lisp ’¥Õ’¥¡’¥¤’¥ë’¤ò byte-compile ’¤¹’¤ë’¤È Mule ’¤È Nemacs ’¤Î’´Ö’¤Ç’¶¦’Í­’¤¹’¤ë’¤³’¤È’¤Ï
’¤Ç’¤­’¤Ê’¤¯’¤Ê’¤ê’¤Þ’¤¹’¡£

@example
; sample .emacs

; Lisp ’¥é’¥¤’¥Ö’¥é’¥ê’¤Î load path ’¤Ë "~/elisp" ’¤ò’ÄÉ’²Ã’¤·’¤Þ’¤¹’¡£
(setq load-path (cons (expand-file-name "~/elisp") 
                        load-path))

; ’¥Ç’¥£’¥¹’¥×’¥ì’¥¤’¤Ë’É½’¼¨’¤¹’¤ë’¤È’¤­’¤Î’Ê¸’»ú’¥³’¡¼’¥É’¤ò’Æü’ËÜ’¸ì EUC ’¤Ë’¤·’¤Þ’¤¹’¡£
(cond ((boundp 'NEMACS) (setq kanji-display-code 3))
      ((boundp 'MULE)
       (set-display-coding-system *euc-japan*)))

; ’¿·’¥Ð’¥Ã’¥Õ’¥¡’ºî’À®’»þ’¤Î’¥Õ’¥¡’¥¤’¥ë’Ê¸’»ú’¥³’¡¼’¥É’¤ò *euc-japan* ’¤Ë’¤·’¤Þ’¤¹’¡£
(if (boundp 'MULE)
    (set-default-file-coding-system *euc-japan*))

; MH ’¤Î’¥×’¥í’¥°’¥é’¥à’¤È’¤ä’¤ê’¤È’¤ê’¤¹’¤ë’¤È’¤­’¤Î’Ê¸’»ú’¥³’¡¼’¥É’¤ò JIS ’¤Ë’»Ø’Äê’¤·’¤Þ’¤¹’¡£
(if (boundp 'MULE)
    (progn
      (define-program-coding-system nil ".*scan.*" (cons *junet* *junet*))
      (define-program-coding-system nil ".*inc.*" (cons *junet*
*junet*))))
(if (boundp 'NEMACS)
    (progn
      (define-program-kanji-code nil ".*scan.*" 2)
      (define-program-kanji-code nil ".*inc.*" 2)))

; Text ’¥â’¡¼’¥É’¤Ë’¤¹’¤ë’¤È’¤­’¡¢’¾ï’¤Ë auto-fill-mode ’¤Ë’¤·’¤Þ’¤¹’¡£
(setq text-mode-hook
      '(lambda () (auto-fill-mode 1)))

; mail-mode ’¤Ë’¤·’¤¿’¤È’¤­’¤Ë’¡¢’¥Õ’¥¡’¥¤’¥ë’Ê¸’»ú’¥³’¡¼’¥É’¤ò JIS ’¤Ë’¥»’¥Ã’¥È’¤¹’¤ë’¤è’¤¦’¤Ë’¤·
; ’¤Þ’¤¹’¡£
(setq mail-mode-hook
      '(lambda ()
	 (setq kanji-fileio-code 2)  ; for Nemacs
	 (if (boundp 'MULE)
	     (set-file-coding-system *junet*))))

; GNUS ’ÍÑ’¤Î’Àß’Äê’¤ò’¹Ô’¤¤’¤Þ’¤¹’¡£
; ’Ãí:’É¬’¤º’³Æ’¥µ’¥¤’¥È’ÍÑ’¤Î’Àß’Äê’¤Ë’½ñ’¤­’Ä¾’¤·’¤Æ’¤¯’¤À’¤µ’¤¤’¡£
(setq gnus-nntp-server "newshost")
(autoload 'gnus "gnus" "Read network news." t)
(autoload 'gnus-post-news "gnuspost" "Post a new news." t)
(setq gnus-your-domain "your.domain.address")
(setq gnus-nntp-service "nntp")
(setq gnus-use-generic-from t)

; BS (C-h) ’¥­’¡¼’¤È DEL ’¥­’¡¼’¤ò’Æþ’¤ì’¤«’¤¨’¤Þ’¤¹’¡£
(load-library "term/bobcat")

@end example

